<item>
            <title>[FLINK-17816] Change Latency Marker to work with &quot;scheduleAtFixedDelay&quot; instead of &quot;scheduleAtFixedRate&quot;</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-17816</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Latency Markers and other periodic timers are scheduled with &lt;tt&gt;scheduleAtFixedRate&lt;/tt&gt;. That means every X time the callable is called. If it blocks (backpressure) is can be called immediately again.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I would suggest to switch this to &lt;tt&gt;scheduleAtFixedDelay&lt;/tt&gt;  to avoid calling for a lot of latency marker injections when there is no way to actually execute the injection call.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13305981">FLINK-17816</key>
